---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import face from '../assets/images/portrait.png';
---

<section class="about">
  <p>
    <Image src={face} alt="portrait" width={100} class="portrait" />
    Ahoy, I'm Wylie!
  </p>
  <p>I'm a dad and a partner. I love Lego, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/wyliefisher" target="_blank" data-track-link="goodreads">books</a>, animals, and the kind of everyday creativity that shows up in gardens, campfires, board games, and building things with your hands. Our home is shared with two cats, a dog named Meatball, and a few other tiny lives, with chickens still high on the wish list.</p>
  <p>Most days, you'll find me thinking about how to create spaces that feel welcoming, thoughtful, and alive. My work centers on running and shaping a community facility built around movement, exploration, and connection. I live at the intersection of operations, creativity, and people, building systems that support others, shaping experiences that feel intentional, and helping turn big ideas into places that matter.</p>
  <p>I'm not actively programming anymore, but I still carry the heart of a front-end developer. That background in structure, clarity, and problem-solving deeply informs how I approach everything I do today, from refining processes to designing programs to thinking about growth. I care about accessibility, sustainability, and creating environments where people feel safe to try, fail, learn, and belong.</p>
  <p>At my core, I'm guided by a commitment to fairness, curiosity, generosity, and honesty. Whether I'm tending a garden bed, smoothing out a workflow, or welcoming someone through the door, I'm always trying to leave things a little better than I found them.</p>
  <p>If you're curious about what I'm building, or just want to say hello, <a href="mailto:me@wyliefisher.com" data-track-link="email-about">I'd love to connect</a>.</p>
</section>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-track-link]').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        const linkId = (e.currentTarget as HTMLElement).getAttribute('data-track-link');
        const w = window as any;
        if (typeof w.gtag !== 'undefined') {
          w.gtag('event', 'link_click', {
            link_id: linkId,
            link_url: (e.currentTarget as HTMLAnchorElement).href
          });
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: left;
    margin-right: 1rem;
  }
  p:not(:first-child) {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
</style>